  "prompt": "What makes mayonnaise a dairy product?",
  "response": "Mayonnaise is not considered a dairy product. It is primarily an emulsion made from oil, egg yolks, vinegar or lemon juice, and various seasonings. The confusion might arise from the creamy texture and richness of mayonnaise, which can be similar to some dairy-based products. However, since mayonnaise does not contain milk or any milk-derived ingredients, it is classified as a condiment rather than a dairy product.",
